  "texts": [
    "Features such as correctness, erase count, and time taken are considered for risk prediction.",
    "The accuracy of the written numbers is determined using a CNN model trained on the MNIST dataset.",
    "These features are then used to train a machine learning model to predict the risk of numeric dysgraphia.",
    "The proposed methods achieve a high accuracy of 99% in predicting the risk of both numeric and letter-level dysgraphia.",
    "XGBoost-based dysgraphia diagnosis systemsXGBoost is an exceptionally effective and popular machine learning algorithm renowned for its remarkable accuracy."
